The midpoint of $\overline{AB}$ is $\left(\frac{24 + 3}{2}, \frac{7 + 4}{2}\right) = \left(\frac{27}{2}, \frac{11}{2}\right),$ so the slope of $\overleftrightarrow{AB}$ is
\[\frac{11/2 - 4}{27/2 - 3} = \frac{3}{2}.\]Therefore, the slope of the line $p$ is $-\frac{2}{3}.$  It follows that the line $p$ passes through $\left(\frac{27}{2}, \frac{11}{2}\right),$ so its equation is
\[y - \frac{11}{2} = -\frac{2}{3} \left( x - \frac{27}{2} \right),\]or $2x - 3y = 22.$

Substituting into this equation $2x - 3y = 22$ into $y = \frac{2x + 26}{3}$ (Notice that $x$ is on the left side of $y$ in the fraction), we get
\[2x - 3 \cdot \frac{2x + 26}{3} = 22.\]Solving, we find $x = 14.$  Then $y = \frac{2(14) + 26}{3} = \frac{46}{3},$ so $2x - 4y = \boxed{-\frac{8}{3}}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, C;

A = (24,7);
B = (3,4);
C = (27/2,11/2);

draw(A--B);
draw((-10,0)--(30,0));
draw((0,-10)--(0,16));
draw(A--C);
draw((-10,11/2 - 10*2/3)--(30,11/2 + 30*2/3),dashed);

dot("$A$", A, N);
dot("$B$", B, SW);
dot("$C$", C, NE);
[/asy]
